The room was very comfortable, with a newly renovated bathroom, comfortable beds, smooth linens, cold A/C, and plentiful TV channels to surf while we recovered. One downside is that this hotel is not located in an ideal place to walk to find food or supplies. However, we took full advantage of the Repsol station across the street, grabbing snacks and sandwich making supplies and drinks so we could just relax in the hotel. The receptionists were also very helpful. The next day our flight did not leave until late in the evening, so the front desk offered to hold our luggage in a locked closet while we went into the city using the city bus that stops right outside the hotel. They even helped us print our bus tour tickets. We were able to come back to the hotel after a day of sightseeing and charge our phones before hopping back on the shuttle to the airport. All in all, kept us sane during a difficult journey home.

    Sants-Montjuc

    Sants-Montjuc centers on Montjuc hill, which offers sweeping sea views from Montjuc Castle and city vistas from paths near the Olympic Stadium. The area is home to cultural institutions like the Joan Mir Foundation, in a striking modernist building, and the Museu Nacional d'Art de Catalunya, in a neoclassical palace. Gardens and pine-filled parks cover the hill, while cable cars connect it to the city and harbor.

    About this hotel

    This relaxed hotel is 10 km from BarcelonaEl Prat Airport and 13 km from Playa de la Barceloneta beach.

    Simply furnished rooms feature complimentary Wi-Fi, as well as flat-screen TVs and minibars.

    An airport shuttle is free. A bright restaurant/lounge features floor-to-ceiling windows, terrace dining and international cuisine; a breakfast buffet is offered (surcharge). There's a fitness room, an indoor pool and a sauna. Coin-operated laundry facilities are available, and pets are welcome (fee).
